SIMPLE: grizzle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Grizzle
<hw>Griz"zle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>gris</ets>:
cf. <ets>grisaille</ets> hair partly gray, fr. <ets>gris</ets> gray. See
<er>Gris</er>, and cf. <er>Grisaille</er>.]</ety> <def>Gray; a gray
color; a mixture of white and black.</def> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grizzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Grizzle
<hw>Griz"zle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To make or
become grizzly, or grayish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>Hardship of the way such as would <qex>grizzle</qex> little
children.</q> <rj><qau>R. F. Burton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>I found myself on the Nubian desert shaking hands with a⟦br⟧
<qex>grizzling</qex> man whom men addressed as Collins Bey.</q>
<rj><qau>Pall Mall Mag.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grizzle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Grizzle
<hw>Griz"zle</hw>, <pos>v. i. & t.</pos> <ety>[Etym. uncertain.]</ety>
<def>To worry; to fret; to bother; grumble.</def> <mark>[Prov.
Eng.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Don't sit <xex>grizzling</xex> there.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Charles Reade.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Grizzled</ent>⟦br⟧
